  "instruction": "Bootstrap a new project using the team configuration at ~/Desktop/team_config.json. This file defines the project name, editor tab size, directories to exclude in VS Code, and a documentation URL. Your tasks: (1) Open the config file in Chrome via its file:// URL so you can review it. (2) Create the project directory ~/Desktop/<projectName>/ (use the name from the config: 'DataPipeline') and create a README.md inside it containing the single line '# DataPipeline'. (3) Configure VS Code User Settings: set editor.tabSize to the value from the config, and add all three directories from excludeDirs to files.exclude (each mapped to true). (4) Open the repoDocsUrl from the config in a new Chrome tab.",
